{"TopicId":197164,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.8.0 - 1.12.x] AltimeterAutoHide (v1.4)","CreatedByName":"todi","CreatedById":135653,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-27T22:42:10Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"todi","CreatedById":135653,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-27T22:42:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbout:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA small mod that hides the altimeter during flight to save screen estate.\u003Cbr\u003E\nMove your mouse to the top edge (where the altimeter usually is) to access the recover/abort/gear/etc buttons.\u003Cbr\u003E\nYou can temporarily disable the auto-hide function by right-clicking on the altimeter. Right-click again to reenable it.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI recommend using mods like \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/jrbudda/KerbalEngineer\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EKerbal Engineer Redux\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/MuMech/MechJeb2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMechJeb\u003C/a\u003E or \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/169611-*\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ESpeed Unit Annex\u003C/a\u003E to display the altitude information in a more space-efficient manner.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf you need even more space: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/174445-19x-*\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EQuickHide\u003C/a\u003E does a similar thing for the stock toolbar and the staging list.\u003Cbr\u003E\nWorks also well with \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/andrew-vant/dragalt\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EDraggable Altimeter\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022demo.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022384\u0022 width=\u0022512\u0022 src=\u0022https://raw.githubusercontent.com/todi/AltimeterAutoHide/master/demo.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDownloads:\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/todi/AltimeterAutoHide/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E GitHub\u003C/a\u003E - \u003Ca href=\u0022https://spacedock.info/mod/2541/AltimeterAutoHide\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESpaceDock\u003C/a\u003E - \u003Cspan\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELinks\u003C/strong\u003E: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/todi/AltimeterAutoHide\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESource\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0- \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/todi/AltimeterAutoHide/issues\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EIssues\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELicence\u003C/strong\u003E: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/todi/AltimeterAutoHide/blob/master/LICENSE\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMIT\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-07-01T08:32:59Z\u0022 title=\u002207/01/2021 08:32  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 1, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by todi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Ecompatible with KSP 1.12.x\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"john hunter","CreatedById":207127,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-28T05:25:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncongrats on the release will defenatly use this mod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"todi","CreatedById":135653,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-28T12:55:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENew Release v1.1\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nSupported KSP versions: 1.8.0 - 1.10.x\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdded version file for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"todi","CreatedById":135653,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-28T13:36:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENew Release v1.2\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nFixed errors in version file\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theJesuit","CreatedById":122369,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-03T18:53:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThats great!\u00A0 Thank you very much!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPeace.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"flart","CreatedById":181486,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-08T00:13:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223860401\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221601246530\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135653\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022todi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/28/2020 at 1:42 AM, todi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmods like \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/jrbudda/KerbalEngineer\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EKerbal Engineer Redux\u003C/a\u003E or \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/MuMech/MechJeb2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMechJeb\u003C/a\u003E to display the altitude information in a more space-efficient manner.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022181486\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3644640265\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/169611-18-speed-unit-annex-%E2%80%94-enhanced-navball-panel-contextually-2019-10-18/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:213px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"todi","CreatedById":135653,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-08T06:01:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181486-flart/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022181486\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181486-flart/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@flart\u003C/a\u003E! I didn\u0027t know about Speed Unit Annex. I\u0027ve added it to the post.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Miguelsgamingch","CreatedById":201607,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-13T01:09:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod is really helpful \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-13T01:41:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is great, but is there any way to keep it open, say, for a maneuver such as landing?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"todi","CreatedById":135653,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-13T06:47:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223866928\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221602553316\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is great, but is there any way to keep it open, say, for a maneuver such as landing?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot yet, because I always have Mechjebs altitude info open. But I could add something. Maybe right-clicking to stick/unstick it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lemon cup","CreatedById":199693,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-13T06:57:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223866984\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221602571652\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135653\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022todi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, todi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot yet, because I always have Mechjebs altitude info open. But I could add something. Maybe right-clicking to stick/unstick it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that would be a good idea as well. Maybe for those\u00A0interested in the mod because they\u2019d like to\u00A0have a cleaner screen when on-orbit,\u00A0and not necessarily because they are running mods with external altitude readouts.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-13T11:49:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223866984\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221602571652\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135653\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022todi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, todi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot yet, because I always have Mechjebs altitude info open. But I could add something. Maybe right-clicking to stick/unstick it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would work pretty well\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"todi","CreatedById":135653,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-13T15:45:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENew Release \u003Cs\u003Ev1.3\u003C/s\u003E v1.4\u003Csup\u003E*\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nAdded functionality to toggle auto-hide with right click on altimeter.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdded option to config.xml to start with auto-hide disabled on flight scene load.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E*\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003E 1.4 is functionally the same as 1.3 and only exists because I suck at release management\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-10-13T16:40:06Z\u0022 title=\u002210/13/2020 04:40  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 13, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by todi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"todi","CreatedById":135653,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-22T10:02:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just checked: 1.4 continues to work with KSP 1.11.0 without changes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}